#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.29:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Puggalavagga"
msgstr "3. Persons"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Andhasutta"
msgstr "29. Blind"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.129"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“These three kinds of people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an3.29:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.29:1.3"
msgid "Andho, ekacakkhu, dvicakkhu."
msgstr "The blind, the one-eyed, and the two-eyed."

msgctxt "an3.29:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo andho?"
msgstr "Who is the blind person?"

#. VAR: phātiṃ kareyya → phātikareyya (bj)
msgctxt "an3.29:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tathārūpaṃ cakkhu na hoti yathārūpena "
"cakkhunā anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigaccheyya adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ "
"kareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who doesn’t have the kind of vision that’s needed to acquire "
"more wealth or to increase the wealth they’ve already acquired."

msgctxt "an3.29:1.6"
msgid ""
"tathārūpampissa cakkhu na hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā kusalākusale dhamme "
"jāneyya, sāvajjānavajje dhamme jāneyya, hīnappaṇīte dhamme jāneyya, "
"kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme jāneyya."
msgstr ""
"Nor do they have the kind of vision that’s needed to know the difference "
"between qualities that are skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and "
"blameless, inferior and superior, and those on the side of dark and bright."

msgctxt "an3.29:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo andho."
msgstr "This is called a blind person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo ekacakkhu?"
msgstr "Who is the person with one eye?"

#. VAR: phātiṃ kareyya → phāti kareyya (bj)
msgctxt "an3.29:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tathārūpaṃ cakkhu hoti yathārūpena "
"cakkhunā anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigaccheyya adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ "
"kareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who has the kind of vision that’s needed to acquire more wealth "
"and to increase the wealth they’ve already acquired."

#. VAR: tathārūpaṃ panassa → tathārūpampissa (bj, s2, s3, km, pts1, mr) | tathārūpassa (s1)
msgctxt "an3.29:2.3"
msgid ""
"tathārūpaṃ panassa cakkhu na hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā kusalākusale dhamme "
"jāneyya, sāvajjānavajje dhamme jāneyya, hīnappaṇīte dhamme jāneyya, "
"kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme jāneyya."
msgstr ""
"But they don’t have the kind of vision that’s needed to know the difference "
"between qualities that are skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and "
"blameless, inferior and superior, and those on the side of dark and bright."

msgctxt "an3.29:2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo ekacakkhu."
msgstr "This is called a one-eyed person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo dvicakkhu?"
msgstr "Who is the person with two eyes?"

msgctxt "an3.29:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tathārūpaṃ cakkhu hoti yathārūpena "
"cakkhunā anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigaccheyya, adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ "
"kareyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who has the kind of vision that’s needed to acquire more wealth "
"and to increase the wealth they’ve already acquired."

msgctxt "an3.29:3.3"
msgid ""
"tathārūpampissa cakkhu hoti yathārūpena cakkhunā kusalākusale dhamme jāneyya;"
msgstr ""
"And they have the kind of vision that’s needed to know the difference "
"between skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and blameless, inferior and "
"superior, or qualities on the side of dark and bright."

msgctxt "an3.29:3.4"
msgid ""
"sāvajjānavajje dhamme jāneyya, hīnappaṇīte dhamme jāneyya, "
"kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme jāneyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.29:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo dvicakkhu."
msgstr "This is called a two-eyed person."

msgctxt "an3.29:3.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti."
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.1"
msgid "Na ceva bhogā tathārūpā,"
msgstr "“Neither suitable wealth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.2"
msgid "na ca puññāni kubbati;"
msgstr "nor merit do they make."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.3"
msgid "Ubhayattha kaliggāho,"
msgstr "They lose on both counts,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:4.4"
msgid "andhassa hatacakkhuno."
msgstr "those blind, with ruined eyes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:5.1"
msgid "Athāparāyaṃ akkhāto,"
msgstr "And now the one-eyed"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:5.2"
msgid "Ekacakkhu ca puggalo;"
msgstr "person is explained."

#. <br>
#. VAR: saṭhoso → sasaṭho (bj) | saṃsaṭṭho (s1-3, km, pts1) | saṭhoti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.29:5.3"
msgid "Dhammādhammena saṭhoso,"
msgstr "By methods good and bad,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:5.4"
msgid "Bhogāni pariyesati."
msgstr "that devious person seeks wealth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.1"
msgid "Theyyena kūṭakammena,"
msgstr "Both by fraudulent, thieving deeds,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.2"
msgid "musāvādena cūbhayaṃ;"
msgstr "and also by lies,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: saṅghātuṃ → saṃhātuṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.29:6.3"
msgid "Kusalo hoti saṅghātuṃ,"
msgstr "the young man’s expert at piling up money,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.4"
msgid "kāmabhogī ca mānavo;"
msgstr "and enjoying sensual pleasures."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.5"
msgid "Ito so nirayaṃ gantvā,"
msgstr "From here they go to hell—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:6.6"
msgid "ekacakkhu vihaññati."
msgstr "the one-eyed person is ruined."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.1"
msgid "Dvicakkhu pana akkhāto,"
msgstr "And now the two-eyed is explained,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.2"
msgid "seṭṭho purisapuggalo;"
msgstr "the best individual."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.3"
msgid "Dhammaladdhehi bhogehi,"
msgstr "Their wealth is properly earned,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:7.4"
msgid "uṭṭhānādhigataṃ dhanaṃ."
msgstr "money acquired by their own hard work."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.130"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.1"
msgid "Dadāti seṭṭhasaṅkappo,"
msgstr "They give with best of intentions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.2"
msgid "abyaggamānaso naro;"
msgstr "that peaceful-hearted person."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.3"
msgid "Upeti bhaddakaṃ ṭhānaṃ,"
msgstr "They go to a good place,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:8.4"
msgid "yattha gantvā na socati."
msgstr "where there is no sorrow."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.1"
msgid "Andhañca ekacakkhuñca,"
msgstr "The blind and the one-eyed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.2"
msgid "ārakā parivajjaye;"
msgstr "you should avoid from afar."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.3"
msgid "Dvicakkhuṃ pana sevetha,"
msgstr "But you should keep the two-eyed close,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.29:9.4"
msgid "seṭṭhaṃ purisapuggalan”ti."
msgstr "the best individual.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.29:9.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
